otivational speaker who addresses issues such as the environment, anti-[[bullying]], and social justice.<ref>[http://urbanmoms.ca/entertainment/the-cool-dad-eric-alper/ His 10 year-old daughter Hannah is that she gets to backstage access to some amazing people] Retrieved 16 November 2016</ref> Alper's grandfather opened Grossman's Tavern in 1943, which is [[Toronto]]'s first licensed [[Blues|blues bar]].<ref>[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/grossmans-bar-crazy-but-in-the-nicest-way/article743508/Grossman's bar: Crazy, but in the nicest way] Retrieved 16 November 2016</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alper, Eric}}\n[[Category:Writers from Toronto]]\n[[Category:Canadian music journalists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Eric Alper\n| image         = EricAlp.jpg\n| alt           =\n| caption       =\n| birth_name    = Eric Alper\n| birth_date    =\n| birth_place   =\n| death_date    =  \n| death_place   =\n| nationality   = Canadian\n| other_names   =\n| occupation    = [[Music correspondent]], [[radio host]], [[blogger]]\n| years_active  = 1995-present\n| known_for     =\n| website       = {{URL|www.thatericalper.com/|Official website}}\n}}\n\n'''Eric Alper''' is a Canadian [[music correspondent]], [[blogger]], [[radio host]] and former [[Director (business)|director]] of [[media relations]] at [[Entertainment One Music|eOne Music Canada]] based in [[Toronto, Ontario]].<ref>[http://www1.toronto.ca/wps/portal/contentonly?vgnextoid=66375213cac14410VgnVCM10000071d60f89RCRD&vgnextchannel=401132d0b6d1e310VgnVCM10000071d60f89RCRD Eric Alper is the Director of Media Relations for eOne Music Canada, and CTV's music correspondent] Retrieved 16 November 2016</ref><ref>[http://junoawards.ca/juno-tv/videos/eric-alper-what-are-you-reading/  What Are You Reading?. Artists: Eric Alper.] Retrieved 16 Nove